The paper deals with the problem of maintaining security of cyber-physical systems under cyber attacks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, since the paper focuses on secure estimation methods for cyber-physical systems, it is most likely to belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category, followed by cryptography and security (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
